{
  "stem": "13079.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And knowing that war crimes were committed when there were violations of the laws and usages of war, we had to frame our charges to come within the limitations of our jurisdictional power.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that we did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that, of course, involved language that was appropriate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had problems to the extent that not all the people served in any one place, any one camp, the whole time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a turnover.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, it would be hard to charge them with conspiracy, because it would be hard to prove a-- an agreement, for example, between the SS, who were the guardians at the camps-- and when I say SS, I mean, actually, they were what was known as the Totenkopfverbande, the Death Head Units of the SS.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And kapos-- kapos were habitual-- usually-- habitual German prisoners.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In Germany at that time, when a prisoner had served his time in the penitentiary and was eligible for release, he wasn't sent back to the community.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was sent to the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that these habitual German criminals were tapped as a source of leadership, in the sense that they were the lowest bases in the leadership operations.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in that sense, the kapos were like the foreman or the leader of a work gang with this important exception-- the kapo had the power of life and death over the prisoners who were working in his group.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, as I said, because of the period of time and the physical locations of the different camps and sub-camps that made up the camp-- like Dachau had 160-odd sub-camps.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mauthausen, even more.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you couldn't really prove a conspiracy, so that was out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, what collective crime have they committed?",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
